    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3213823084" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3213823084" />
    <a title="Christopher Robinson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/62328457-christopher-robinson"><img alt="Christopher Robinson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1503277082p2/62328457.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3213823084?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christopher Robinson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christopher Robinson" href="/user/show/62328457-christopher-robinson">Christopher Robinson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/15719405-by-night-in-chile">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/62328457-christopher-robinson?shelf=read-2020">read-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/62328457-christopher-robinson?shelf=read-and-kept">read-and-kept</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/62328457-christopher-robinson?shelf=very-favorite-novels">very-favorite-novels</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3213823084" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11511534021888365684">I knew next to nothing about the contents of this book when I started in on it, just that it consisted of a single long paragraph and concerned a priest recounting his collaboration with the Pinochet regime. Good enough for me. And so I proceeded. It ended up being quite a ride, beautiful and funny and dark and horrible and depressing all at once. Fantastic writing, also, of course. It’s Bolaño after all. I’ll single out one particular section as being my personal favorite: there is a very long </span>
  <span id="freeText11511534021888365684" style="display:none">I knew next to nothing about the contents of this book when I started in on it, just that it consisted of a single long paragraph and concerned a priest recounting his collaboration with the Pinochet regime. Good enough for me. And so I proceeded. It ended up being quite a ride, beautiful and funny and dark and horrible and depressing all at once. Fantastic writing, also, of course. It’s Bolaño after all. I’ll single out one particular section as being my personal favorite: there is a very long sentence that runs from page 81 - 82 (in this edition, the New Directions paperback) in which the entire chunk of history from Allende’s election through Pinochet’s coup occurs in the background while the narrator keeps to himself and rereads basically the entirety of Classical Greek literature. What happens from that point on I’ll shut up about and let you experience for yourself. You owe it to yourself to read By Night in Chile. It’s an incredible experience. <br /><br />(It is also worth mentioning that the English translation by Chris Andrews is magnificent. There is no clunkiness or awkwardness at all, it flows effortlessly. It is one of those translations that compels me to dream longingly of having endless amounts of free time in which to learn languages and experience these works of world literature in their original form.)</span>
  <a data-text-id="11511534021888365684" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

